🧠 Verdict

👍 A surprisingly capable low-power APU system, particularly under Linux.
💻 Browser and productivity benchmarks are strong — WebGL runs smoothly.
🎮 Minecraft and lighter 3D games are playable, but heavier titles show limits.
🔥 Thermal and power behavior remain efficient, even under full load.
❌ GPU bottlenecks evident in shader-heavy or AAA scenarios.

---

📝 Tester Notes

> “Linux performance is smoother and lighter; Minecraft feels native. MX83 shows strong iGPU physics response. Windows handles games better overall but draws more power. CPU performs beyond expectation for a 35W-class chip.”

